    <div class="w3-col m6 w3-padding-large w3-hide-small">
     <img src="/photos/morefood.jpeg" class="w3-round w3-image w3-opacity-min" width="900" height="750">
    </div>

    <div class="w3-col m6 w3-padding-large">
      <h1 class="w3-center">About Recipe Vision</h1><br>
      <h5 class="w3-center">A Passion for Food & Cooking</h5>
      <p class="w3-large">We were inspired to create this as part of a project for our Software Engineering class. It is brought to you by Brian, Ryan, Monique, & Kristine. Among our many brilliant ideas, we felt strongest about this one. <b>Who doesn't love food?!</b> We were motivated by our passion for food, and know that many users would also enjoy this idea. The way they will get to search for recipes through the use of text and images,it is different from other websites. We want the users to feel just as excited about food and cooking as we are.</p>
     </br>
     
      <h5 class="w3-center">Overall Goals</h5>
      <p class="w3-large w3-text-grey w3-hide-medium">The goal was to deliver an application that could search for recipes using manually typed searches as well as pictures of food. The web application can allow users to use their own photos of food to find recipes for that particular dish. Users will be able to find real, trusted recipes that are pulled from a Recipe Search API called <a href="https://developer.edamam.com/">Edamam</a>. Once users have found recipes that they desire, they can choose to save the recipes in what we call a `recipe book`. Later on we plan to have users share recipes and chat to other users based on what they saved. </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <hr>
