  <center><img src="/photos/spice.jpeg" class="w3-round w3-opacity-min" width="950" height="500"></center>

  <hr>
  
  <!-- Menu Section -->
  <div class="w3-row w3-padding-63" id="works">
    <div class="w3-col l6 w3-padding-large">
      <h1 class="w3-center">How It Works</h1>
      
      <p>We are able to make our project work through quite a few approaches and technologies. The framework we used was Node.js & Express. The IDE we used was Cloud9. The main API's we used are Edamam API, & Google Vision API. Finally, we deployed the website on Heroku.</p>
     </br>
      <h4>Heroku</h4>
      <p class="w3-text-grey">We are using Heroku in order to host our application.</p>
        
      <h4>Edamam API</h4>
      <p class="w3-text-grey">With this API, it provides a vast amount of recipes including pictures, calories and source links.</p>
      
      <h4>Youtube API</h4>
      <p class="w3-text-grey">Allows us to pull recipe videos relevent to the searches</p>

      <h4>Google Vision API</h4>
      <p class="w3-text-grey">Through this API, it grabs the contents of an image, which allows for the recipe search.</p><br>
    
      <h4 href="/features"><b>Try it Out!</b></h4>
